The five-year accident history:

This facility has had two accidental releases subject to EPA 40 CFR Part 68 within the last five years. On 2/21/18 a truck driver injured his forearm while unloading anhydrous ammonia from his truck to our truck rack. A small amount of ammonia impacted his forearm at the interface of the sleeves of his chemical resistant suits long sleeves and the chemical resistant gloves. The injury was classified as medical treatment. On 2/23/18, there was a release of approximately 415 pounds of anhydrous ammonia to the atmosphere from the flare stack due to the failure of liquid level sensing equipment in a process vessel. An industrial neighbor ordered some of their employees to shelter-in-place as a precaution.



The emergency response program:

